{"word":"H5397 - נְשָׁמָה - nᵉshâmâh - nesh-aw-maw' - Blast","slug":"H5397","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">נְשָׁמָה</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>nᵉshâmâh"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>nesh-aw-maw'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Blast"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E0;&#x05E9;&#x05C1;&#x05DE;&#x05D4; - n<sup>e</sup>sha&#x0302;ma&#x0302;h</b> - <i>nesh-aw-maw'</i><p/>From <a href=\"#/H5395\">H5395</a>; a <i>puff</i>, that is, <i>wind</i>, angry or vital <i>breath</i>, divine <i>inspiration</i>, <i>intellect</i> or (concretely) an <i>animal: - </i>blast, (that) breath (-eth), inspiration, soul, spirit."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5395\">H5395</a>, <a href=\"#/H8580\">H8580</a>"}]}